{
  "stem": "2522.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Hashomer Hatzair thing was really based on the kibbutz, on the collective of kibbutz, and going back to an agricultural base, which was not-- was not the ideology of Betar.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, there was no underlying economic or social ideology of Betar other than aggressive takeover and seizing the land.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I guess that was one of the distinctions that I remember.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we, we started sensing the threat maybe as early as '36 but surely in '37, when a stream of refugees started coming from Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My house, my father's house was always a way, way station for people going around for various causes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother was the chairman of WIZO, which is the woman's Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father's partner was, in fact, a delegate to the Jewish Congress.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there has always been a very heavy Zionist traffic through our house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Andrew Kubicek, K-U-B-I-C-E-K.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a delegate to the Zionist Congress.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so, so, we already knew in '37 what was happening in Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and the prospects and the future of what would happen to us was widely debated at dinner table.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember a particularly tearful incident where one of my father's best friend divorced his wife because he wanted to leave Trencin, and she didn't want to.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was a totally unheard-of experience.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, in fact, the scene happened in our store after the store closed in the evening.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember it the way it was today.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the scene between this lovely woman-- her name was Sylvia Reidlich, and her husband, Robert Reidlich-- how they came to my father, sort of to, to try to settle their dispute.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
